Installing grafana 

sudo apt-get  update
sudo apt-get install -y adduser libfontconfig1
wget https://dl.grafana.com/oss/release/grafana_8.2.3_amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i grafana_8.2.3_amd64.deb
sudo systemctl start  grafana-server.service

------------------------------------------

Installing Prometheus 

sudo apt install prometheus

sudo service prometheus status

curl http://127.0.0.1:9100/metrics

Then go in grafana server and import the existing dashboards which suits your requirements.

For this purpose of this demonstration I am using the dashboards ID : 11074
-------------------

Installing node exporter on node 02 
sudo apt-get update 
sudo apt install prometheus-node-exporter
sudo service prometheus-node-exporter status
curl http://127.0.0.1:9100/metrics

Now its time to add the other node in the grafana server.

so, we will go to the prometheus server and stop the prometheus service 

sudo vi /etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml

add the target line under the scraping config block 

- target [i.p:9100]

After making the above changes, start the prometheus service and then you will be able to see the dashboards poping up with the data/metrics info of the other node as well.
